# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types (required, pick one):
#   feat      - New feature
#   fix       - Bug fix
#   docs      - Documentation only changes
#   style     - Formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
#   refactor  - Code refactoring
#   test      - Adding or updating tests
#   chore     - Maintenance tasks, dependency updates, etc.
#   perf      - Performance improvement
#   ci        - CI/CD changes
#   revert    - Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope (required):
#   The part of the codebase affected (e.g., auth, api, db, ui, agents, backend, etc.)
#
# Subject (required, max 50 chars):
#   Imperative mood: "Add" not "Added", "Fix" not "Fixed"
#   No period at the end
#   Be specific: "Fix login redirect loop" not "Fix bug"
#
# Body (optional):
#   Explain *why* the change was made, not *what* changed.
#   Include motivation, context, and any important details.
#   Wrap at 72 characters.
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Breaking changes: "BREAKING-CHANGE: description"
#   - Closes issues: "Closes #123, Closes #124"
#   - Related issues: "Related to #123"
#
# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add OAuth2 login support
#   fix(api): handle null response in user endpoint
#
#   The API occasionally returns null for inactive users.
#   Added null check and return 404 for such cases.
#
#   Closes #123
